Springbok pivot Lambie started the game despite his discomfort but was replaced after five minutes by mercurial teenage talent Curwin Bosch, who went on to score 27 points in the match. It is difficult to say exactly the approximate length of recovery will be in Pat s case as he undergoes further scans, but his return is estimated at six to eight weeks, Sharks team doctor Alan Kourie said on the team s website on Monday.Loose-forward Philip van der Walt has also been ruled out of Saturday s home match against the Southern Kings with a fractured cheekbone, while hooker Franco Marais and French fullback Clement Poitrenaud will be assessed ahead of the weekend.